  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
 and <m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>γ</m:mi>
    <m:mo>→</m:mo>
    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>. In this case, the Lorentz transform is reduced to Galilean transform as expected. Further, we can write transformation in the direction from primed to unprimed reference as :
</para>
<para id="element-19a1">

